content: Amazing app with great content. I just wish the database was bigger for this app specifically compared to Pocket Workouts. Also, there seems to be a bug where the app goes to the start menu if you turn it to landscape. Not sure if this is by design.

Support Darebee!  This is a good app for generating random quick exercise challenges.  The website is fantastic and free, so I purchased this app to support them.
Great

I set my time for 20 minutes and do whatever #FitTap tells me.   Great app and very good for muscle confusion.  Buying a shirt in support as well. Working out to add five minutes until I get to 35 minutes 5 to 7 times a week.  For those who want weighted exercises and variations,  its simple to think up something that might work.  With 100 squats I add arm positions,  with leg kicks I kick in different directions, with arm raises I'll pick up five pounds,  it's easy to make this that much more challenging.  #ThanksNeila

Simple and very effective for people who want to stay fit without having to think about what exercise to do next and with how many reps. If you'll do what the app tells you for 30 minutes a day, you'll be super fit and have a top notch body! You can do those anywhere anytime, also during travel!
